{
  "stem": "17301.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He took a lot of merchandise that he had in in business, and in middle of the night, his friend helped him to bring some, some things home like a lot of he had a lot of rice and coffee and flour and sugar.",
      "word_count": 44
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And for later on, he, he had [INAUDIBLE] because he said, probably, we won't be able to go shopping.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And, yeah, that's how he did.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And they closed down our store.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, more or less, yes, without any-- no difficulties.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes, we had because there was a little girl that came to our town.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And my mother asked her to stay with us, live with us.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Her family was killed in Poland.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And she played dead when they were lined up, they were shooting them.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She fell down and she played dead, pretending she was also shot.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And when everybody left, she got up and she was able to get to a little village where somebody helped her to come through the border of Poland, and, and at that time Czechoslovakia.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And she happened to come to our town.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And my mother found out and we kind of embraced her.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And she came to live with us for a while.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They still felt, I mean, my father still felt that it's still Czechoslovakia, you still belonged.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I mean, he didn't belong at that time.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it's such a beautiful country that we shouldn't have anything to worry about, except when we got word from Germany from our uncles.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[BACKROUND NOISE]",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It was too late to flee.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "There was no way of fleeing because they were, they kept a pretty close watch on us.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So we couldn't go anywhere.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "By then, when the German came in, everybody had to give their names and addresses.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
